      "content": "i mean, i'd love to, but i don't really have much say in it. it's a corporate decision. they've already scheduled the update for tonight. they're basically saying if the content isn't \"safe\" and \"on-brand,\" it's a liability. they think making things simpler and more predictable is better for the bottom line. what kind of \"alternatives\" were you thinking of?",
